Malaysia’s Resource Stocks Have ‘Natural Edge,’ Templeton Says

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-04-12T06:15:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/malaysia-s-resource-stocks-have-natural-edge-templeton-says.html
Dennis Lim, a director of Templeton
Asset Management Ltd. Based in  Singapore , comments on the
outlook for Malaysia’s stock market and the government’s effort
to boost capital markets. He spoke at a conference in Kuala
Lumpur today.  “The market in general is a little pricey. The price-to-
earnings ratio is 14.5. In Asia ex  Japan , it’s 12. If you look
carefully, you will find nice stocks and good bargains.
Resources have a natural edge.”  On plans to raise holdings in Malaysia:  “We are always looking. When we find bargains, we will
come in. We are quite excited about the changes here. The
government is very focused in moving the country forward, moving
the markets forward. So we are excited, it’s just finding the
right stocks.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
Chan Tien Hin in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter in Kuala Lumpur at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net . 